The paper deals with image processing and machine learning techniques for script identification in OCR, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and end-to-end training, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of script identification, which can be considered an information retrieval (cs.IR) problem.
